The Telegraph - Calcutta : International

 World Briefs

 Peres for Sharon 

 Tel Aviv, Nov. 30 (Reuters): Veteran Israeli statesman Shimon Peres announced today he was throwing his support behind Prime Minister Ariel Sharon in March elections and ending his own political activity in the Labour Party. 

 Calling Sharon the most suitable person for the job of peacemaking, Peres said: I have therefore decided to support his candidacy and cooperate with him in achieving these objectives. 

 WHO protest 

 Geneva (Reuters): Several hundred World Health Organisation staff halted work for an hour today in an unprecedented protest against job cuts. 

 Bangla move 

 Dhaka (Reuters): Police in Bangladesh said on Wednesday they had detained 22 suspected Islamist militants following suicide bomb attacks at court buildings. 

 Pinter Nobel 

 Stockholm (Reuters): Ill health has forced British playwright Harold Pinter to cancel all public appearances linked to his Nobel Prize for Literature . 

 Author dead 

 New York (Reuters): Stan Berenstain, who with his wife created the popular Berenstain Bears childrens book series, has died in Pennsylvania. He was 82. 




